<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 326.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August 15,</hi> 1862.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Complaints having been made through Mr.
                            Stuart, her Britannic Majesty’s charge d’affaires here, of the exaction
                            of bonds on merchandise exported from New York for Nassau, explanations
                            upon the subject have been requested of the Secretary of the
                            Treasury.</p>
                        <p>A copy of a letter of the 9th instant, from Mr. Harney to Mr. Chase, is
                            herewith enclosed, which contains those explanations. You may, if you
                            deem it necessary or proper, communicate a transcript of the same to
                            Earl Russell.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>